The City of Cisco has started construction on the Wastewater System Improvements projectthrough the CleanWater State Revolving Fund (CWSRF) administered by the Texas Water Development Board. Funded in wholeby CWSRF, the project includes the construction of the WastewaterTreatment Plant and Humbletown Lift Station. The City of Cisco will construct a new Wastewater Treatment Plant through the Clean Water State Revolving Fund (CWSRF) administered by the Texas Water Development Board. The new Wastewater Treatment Plant will be constructed near the existing Wastewater Treatment Plant and will serve the entire City of Cisco.
